; Frame sequences (animation data)
;
; One entry per movement ID. Each sequence is a list of frame indices into
; #R44189 Barbarian sprite pointer table, terminated by a sentinel byte.
;
; .
;
; Note: Drax sprites and animations are present in the data but are never
; triggered in the 2 Players version of the game.
; .
; Terminators:
; .
; #N$FD - LOOP: on the last frame, jump back to the first frame of the
; sequence.
; .
; #N$FE - HOLD: freeze animation advance; the game logic determines when to
; proceed to the next frame.
; .
; #N$FF - CHAIN: end this sequence and chain into another; the following byte
; specifies the target movement ID.
@label=frame_seq
b44501 DEFB 0,0,0,0,0,0,0,0                 ; {#HTML(<span>0
 44509 DEFB 0,0,0,0,0,82,83,84              ; Idle</br>)#IMGW(10)(sprites/000.png)#IMGW(10)(sprites/082.png)#IMGW(10)(sprites/083.png)#IMGW(10)(sprites/084.png)
