; AI profile data blocks.
;
; .
;
; .
;
; 22 blocks of 8 bytes each. Each byte is a movement_block_id (0-22) that
; selects an 8-byte row in #R47974. The column within the profile is chosen by
; #R47578[#R46834] (secondary AI table, range 0-7).
; .
; Profiles with low block IDs (0-6) are passive/defensive.
; .
; Profiles with high block IDs (14-22) are aggressive.
; .
; Most profiles end with [4,8]: block 4 and block 8 are identical (both =
; [1,5,1,1,1,1,1,1], biased toward attack-5 and forward-1).
@label=ai_profile_0
b47798 DEFB 0,1,1,6,6,6,4,8       ;   Profile $BAB6: [0,1,1, 6,6,6, 4,8]
                                  ; passive->neutral->attack
@label=ai_profile_1
 47806 DEFB 22,5,5,20,20,20,4,8   ;   Profile $BABE: [22,5,5, 20,20,20, 4,8]
                                  ; lunge/special
@label=ai_profile_2
 47814 DEFB 0,1,1,13,13,13,4,8    ;   Profile $BAC6: [0,1,1, 13,13,13, 4,8]
                                  ; passive->walk
